Yeah I agree with you here. `__signatures__` should probably be a very quick description of the attribute.

It seems like there are a few issues when indexing fused functions:
* When indexing from Python, or when indexing a `def` fused function from Cython, you must index with Python objects;
* `int` and `float` evaluate as the Python objects `int` and `float` don't let you select their equivalent C types;
* When indexing from Cython, `cython.double` (etc.) aren't available as runtime Python objects;
* When indexing from Python, `cython.double` (etc.) is only available if they have Cython installed, which may not be the case anyway!

The solution to all of this is to index with strings instead.
